# Use Cases Index – Travel Insurance Claim System

This file serves as the **master index of all use cases** for the Travel Insurance Claim System. It includes existing use cases and additional ones that capture all major workflows for customers, agents, and administrators.

---

## Existing Use Cases

| Use Case | File | Description |
|----------|------|-------------|
| Register / Create Account | `Register_Create_Account/README.md` | Customer registers for a new account and sets up profile information. |
| Submit Insurance Claim | `Submit_Insurance_Claim_UseCase.md` | Customer submits a travel insurance claim with supporting documents. |
| View Policy Details | `View_Policy_Details/README.md` | Customer views details of their policies, coverage, and limits. |
| Approve / Process Claims | `Approve - Process Claims/README.md` | Agent reviews submitted claims and approves or rejects them. |
| UAT (User Acceptance Testing) | `UAT/README.md` | Test cases and scenarios for validating the system against requirements. |

---

## New / Additional Use Cases

| Use Case | File | Description |
|----------|------|-------------|
| Update Account / Policy Info | `Update_Account_Policy_Info/README.md` | Customer updates personal information or modifies travel policy details. |
| Request Additional Documents | `Request_Additional_Documents/README.md` | Agent requests extra documents or clarifications from the customer for claims processing. |
| Notifications | `Notifications/README.md` | System sends notifications (email/SMS) for claim submission, approval, rejection, or document requests. |
| Payment Processing / Reimbursement | `Payment_Processing/README.md` | Tracks and processes payments for approved claims, including refunds or reimbursements. |
| Policy Purchase / Renewal | `Policy_Purchase_Renewal/README.md` | Customer purchases a new travel insurance policy or renews an existing one. |
| Reporting & Analytics | `Reporting_Analytics/README.md` | Admin or management generates reports or views dashboards for claims, payments, and system activity. |
| Fraud Detection / Flagging | `Fraud_Detection/README.md` | System identifies and flags suspicious claims for further review. |

